TrpzApInterfaceIndex.name: TrpzApInterfaceIndex
TrpzApInterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each AP network interface.

trpzApIfTable.name: trpzApIfTable
trpzApIfTable.description: A table describing the network interfaces on all the APs currently present and managed by this AC (APs in ''ALIVE'' state).

trpzApIfEntry.name: trpzApIfEntry
trpzApIfEntry.description: Information about a particular network interface on an AP attached to the AC.

trpzApIfApSerialNum.name: trpzApIfApSerialNum
trpzApIfApSerialNum.description: The Serial Number of the AP containing this network interface.

trpzApIfIndex.name: trpzApIfIndex
trpzApIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each AP network interface.

trpzApIfName.name: trpzApIfName
trpzApIfName.description: The textual name of the interface.

trpzApIfType.name: trpzApIfType
trpzApIfType.description: The type of AP network interfaces.

trpzApIfMtu.name: trpzApIfMtu
trpzApIfMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets.

trpzApIfHighSpeed.name: trpzApIfHighSpeed
trpzApIfHighSpeed.description: The nominal bandwidth of AP network interfaces in units of 1,000,000 bits per second.

trpzApIfMac.name: trpzApIfMac
trpzApIfMac.description: The MAC address of this network interface.

trpzApIfCompliance.name: trpzApIfCompliance
trpzApIfCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement AP If MIB. This compliance statement is for releases 7.1 and greater of AC (wireless switch) software.

trpzApIfBasicGroup.name: trpzApIfBasicGroup
trpzApIfBasicGroup.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide basic Interface info in releases 7.1 and greater.
